TerraKulture the home of Nigeria’s contemporary arts and culture has released the official schedule of March and April’s theatrical production. Below is the schedule: FELA AND THE KALAKUTA QUEENS Tells The Untold Story Of The Brave, Stunning and fierce Kalakuta Queens (The 27 wives of Afrobeat King Fela Anikulapo Kuti) Show Starts: March 30 and 31st. April 1,2,7,8,14,15,21,22,28,29th
Time: 3PM and 7PM
Venue: Terra Kulture, Tiamiyu Savage Street, V.I. Lagos <img class="aligncenter wp-image-586499 lazyload" src="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/IMG-20180320-WA0000-e1521734761253-598x598.jpg" alt="" width="1280" height="594" /> SEKI is a pantomimic dance drama tracing the American tap dance to the indigenous people of lower Niger Delta Area of Nigeria. Show Starts: 23rd, 24th and 25th.
Time: 3PM and 7PM
Venue: Terra Kulture, Tiamiyu Savage Street, V.I. Lagos . This dance drama was created and directed by Yibo Koko in association with BAP Productions.